body:
## Context
From PR #289 code review finding.

## Problem
Error details from the underlying HTTP client are returned directly to MCP callers via `fmt.Sprintf("Failed to submit feedback: %v", err)`. This could leak internal URLs, request metadata, or operational details on network failures.

## Current State
Most errors are user-facing (auth expired, validation errors), but network errors could expose internal details.

## Proposed Solution
Return sanitized user-safe error messages and log detailed errors server-side:
```go
if err != nil {
    // Log detailed error for debugging
    log.Printf("feedback submission failed: %v", err)
    // Return safe message to client
    return &mcp.CallToolResult{
        IsError: true,
        Content: []mcp.Content{
            &mcp.TextContent{Text: "Failed to submit feedback. Please try again."},
        },
    }, SubmitFeedbackOutput{}, nil
}
```

## Priority
Low - security hardening, no immediate risk.
